com.bluegosling.apt.reflect

Interface ArAnnotatedElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ArAnnotatedConstruct
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArClass, ArConstructor, ArField, ArMethod, ArPackage, ArParameter, ArTypeParameter

    public interface ArAnnotatedElement
extends ArAnnotatedConstruct
    An element that can have annotations. This includes representations of things in the Java programming language which can be annotated, like packages, types, fields, constructors, methods, and parameters.

    The Java programming language also allows local variables (including exception variables defined in catch blocks) to be annotated, but support for this during annotation processing is incomplete, so there currently are no such implementations.

    This interface is analogous to AnnotatedElement, except that it represents a source-level type (during annotation processing) instead of an actual runtime type. Unlike core reflection, this interface can be used to inspect annotations whose retention policy is RetentionPolicy.CLASS or RetentionPolicy.SOURCE.

    See Also:
    AnnotatedElement, Element
